.TH XIL\-SPLICE "1" "2026\-04\-05" "xil\-pipeline 0.1.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xil\-splice
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xil\-splice
[-h] --episode EPISODE [--show SHOW] [--parsed PARSED] [--insert-after INSERT_AFTER] [--from-parsed FROM_PARSED] [--from-seq-range FROM_SEQ_RANGE] [--from-json FROM_JSON] [--section SECTION] [--scene SCENE] [--delete-seq-range DELETE_SEQ_RANGE] [--dry-run] [--no-backup] [--quiet]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Splice Parsed JSON — insert/delete entries with automatic renumbering

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-episode\fR \fI\,EPISODE\/\fR
Episode tag (e.g. S02E03) — derives target parsed JSON path

.TP
\fB\-\-show\fR \fI\,SHOW\/\fR
Show name override (default: from project.json)

.TP
\fB\-\-parsed\fR \fI\,PARSED\/\fR
Override target parsed JSON path

.TP
\fB\-\-insert\-after\fR \fI\,INSERT_AFTER\/\fR
Seq number to insert after

.TP
\fB\-\-from\-parsed\fR \fI\,FROM_PARSED\/\fR
Source parsed JSON to extract entries from

.TP
\fB\-\-from\-seq\-range\fR \fI\,FROM_SEQ_RANGE\/\fR
Seq range to extract from source (e.g. 232\-233)

.TP
\fB\-\-from\-json\fR \fI\,FROM_JSON\/\fR
Path to a JSON array of entries to insert

.TP
\fB\-\-section\fR \fI\,SECTION\/\fR
Override section on inserted entries

.TP
\fB\-\-scene\fR \fI\,SCENE\/\fR
Override scene on inserted entries

.TP
\fB\-\-delete\-seq\-range\fR \fI\,DELETE_SEQ_RANGE\/\fR
Seq range to delete (e.g. 100\-105)

.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show plan without writing files

.TP
\fB\-\-no\-backup\fR
Skip backup file

.TP
\fB\-\-quiet\fR
Summary only, no per\-entry detail

